  "prompt": "Do different animals see different stars in the sky?",
  "response": "No, animals and humans generally see the same stars in the sky. The visibility of stars depends on factors like:\n\n1. Location on Earth\n2. Time of night\n3. Local light pollution\n4. Individual eye's ability to detect light\n\nHowever, different animals perceive stars differently due to variations in:\n- Visual capabilities\n- Eye structure\n- Color perception\n- Night vision sensitivity\n\nSome animals like cats and owls have better night vision and might see stars more clearly, but the actual stars remain the same. The primary differences are in how clearly or brightly the stars are perceived.",
